- SOA-edit option for dyndns
  A specific soa-edit (SOA-EDIT-2136 ?) could help is tune the SOA-changes that are required after an update.

21:44 < _cyclops_> Add a option to domainmetadata called 'SOA-EDIT-2136', options are:
21:44 < _cyclops_> - DEFAULT - Change serial to YYYYMMDD01. If current serial >= YYYYMMDD01 do
                   current serial+1
21:45 < _cyclops_> - INCREASE - Set the serial to current serial + 1
21:45 < _cyclops_> - SOA-EDIT-INCREASE - Set to whatever SOA-EDIT provides. If the provided <=
                   current serial do current serial+1
21:46 < _cyclops_> - SOA-EDIT - Simply set to whatever SOA-EDIT provides
12:13 <@   Habbie> soa-edit-2136 sounds good
12:13 <@   Habbie> although i'd like a unixtime variant too


